      • deleteNote

        public Note[] deleteNote(Note[] strArray,
                         java.lang.String str,
                         boolean repeat)
        Function for removing notes from array by literal value.
        Parameters:
        strArray - - array of notes.
        str - - literal value of note, which will be deleted from array.
        repeat - - flag of multiple remove. If value of flag is true, then all notes with equal value to "str" will be deleted. If value of flag is false, then first seen note with equal value to "str" will be deleted.
        Returns:
        array without deleted note(s) (note(s) replaced by null).

      • replaceNote

        public Note[] replaceNote(Note[] strArray,
                          java.lang.String currentNote,
                          java.lang.String newNote,
                          boolean repeat)
        Function for replacing notes from array by literal value.
        Parameters:
        strArray - - array of notes.
        currentNote - - literal value of note, which will be replaced in array.
        newNote - - new note.
        repeat - - flag of multiple replace. If value of flag is true, then all notes with equal value to "current note" will be replaced on "newNote". If value of flag is false, then first seen note with equal value to "current note" will be replaced on "newNote"
        Returns:
        array with replaced note(s).
